    "Since for all u ′ ⊑ u, u ′ ̸ ∈ X, and z ≬ u, persistence for X implies z ̸ ∈ X, so z ̸ ∈ X ′ = X ∩ S ′, which with xR ′ i z implies x ̸ ∈ ■ ′ i X ′.To show that F ′ is a possibility frame, it only remains to show that P ′ ⊆ RO(S ′, ⊑ ′).",
